cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with formal verification of a dependent type theory, LF, using a theorem prover. This falls under the category of formal methods and verification, which is covered by cs.LO. The paper also involves type checking algorithms and executable code generation, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of LF as a foundation for other formal systems also relates to logic (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
